==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entomophaga
<hw>En`to*moph"a*ga</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>'e`ntomon</grk> an insect + <grk>fagei^n</grk> to
eat.]</ety> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a group of
hymenopterous insects whose larv⟦ae⟧ feed parasitically upon living
insects. See <er>Ichneumon</er>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A group of marsupials which are partly
insectivorous, as the opossum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A group of edentates, including the
ant-eaters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 498 --></p>

<p><ent>Entomophagan</ent>⟦br⟧
